FBIS4-30962 "dreeu106_i_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-106 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Close to Gorazde Center Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Close to Gorazde Center AU0206104894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 2 Jun 94 AU0206104894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic from Gorazde] [Excerpt] According to information from the surveillance-intelligence unit of the Operative Group East Bosnia of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, the aggressor's units in Gorazde are still 300-400 meters from the town center. This once again proves that the aggressor is deceiving the domestic and international public daily, which requires a more energetic action by the UN Security Council and NATO and calls for an immediate realization of Resolution No. 913 and the NATO ultimatum. Since this morning, the Serbo-Montenegrin fascists have been opening fire from antiaircraft machine guns and antiaircraft guns at Hrenovica and [word indistinct] and from antiaircraft machine guns, [words indistinct] and sniper rifles at Djinjici, Stupi, Brijegi, and [word indistinct]. There are chetnik infantry arms provocations along the Osanica-Ilovaca-Orahovice defense line. [passage omitted]
